===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|dett|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|dete|lang=fro}} (French: {{term|dette|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term|debita|dēbita|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|debitum|dēbitum|what is owed, a debt, a duty|lang=la}}, neuter of {{term|debitus|dēbitus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|debeo|dēbeō|I owe|lang=la}}, contraction of {{term/t|la|*dehibeo|*dehibeō|I have from}}, from {{term|de||from|lang=la}} + {{term|habeo|habeō|I have|lang=la}}.

The unpronounced "b" in the modern English spelling is a [[Latinisation]] from the Latin etymon {{term|debitum|dēbitum|lang=la}}.

